profile_positions.description:
My role at this time was primarily composed of three parts. 

- I supervised students (bachelor level) and developed and taught courses primarily for the international Game Design and Development major programme. The main topics I worked on were (Educational) Game Design, Interaction Design, Design Research, Research Methods, and User-Centered Design;

- I initiatied new research projects for the research group User-Centered Design. These projects focused on understanding the relationship between game mechanics and user effects, virtual reality, and long-term (adaptive) game experiences;

- I was responsible for the management portfolios study quality​ and study efficiency for the study programmes Communication & Multimedia Design and Information Services & Management (on behalf of the management team). In that capacity, I focused on maintaining high educational standards, while ensuring that students were supported adequately throughout their study programme.
